Convert each SWOT quadrant into actions: Strengths → 2 leverage plays (double down on what works); Weaknesses → 2 remediation tasks (close critical gaps); Opportunities → 2 growth bets (pursue highest-ROI openings); Threats → 2 defensive moves (mitigate top risks). For each of the 8 actions, define: owner, specific deliverable, success metric (quantified), required resources, and milestone date within the 90-day window. Sequence them across three 30-day sprints: Days 1–30 focus on quick wins and remediation, Days 31–60 on growth bets and capability building, Days 61–90 on scaling what worked and consolidating defenses. Hold a weekly 30-minute review against metrics, and a checkpoint at Day 45 to kill or double-down on each initiative. Cap WIP at 3 active actions per sprint to avoid dilution. Output as a single table: Action | SWOT source | Owner | Metric | Sprint | Due date.
